TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bechtel, Alexander
AU  - Ranaldo, Angelo
AU  - Wrampelmeyer, Jan
T1  - Liquidity Risk and Funding Cost
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfac020
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
SP  - 399
EP  - 422
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We propose and test a new channel that links liquidity risk and interest rates in short-term funding markets. Unlike existing theories that focus on premiums demanded by lenders, the liquidity risk channel postulates that borrowers that are more exposed to urgent liquidity needs are willing to pay a markup for immediate funding. We test and quantify the channel using unique trade-by-trade data and uncover systematic differences across individual banks’ funding cost driven by differences in banks’ liquidity risk. These differences are persistent over a decade, suggesting that the liquidity risk channel is relevant in general and not only arises during crisis times.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfac020
ER  - 



